## Migration Guide

### For Users

**No action required**: The smoke test command remains the same:
```bash
cargo run -p scriptbots-world-gfx --bin wgpu_triangle
```

Visual behavior is identical to the previous version.

### For Developers Copying This Code

**Before** (if you copied old wgpu_triangle):
```rust
fn main() {
    pollster::block_on(run());
}

async fn run() {
    let event_loop = EventLoop::new()?;
    let window = event_loop.create_window(...)?;

    // ... initialize wgpu ...

    event_loop.run(move |event, target| {
        // Handle all events in closure
    })?;
}
```

**After** (copy new wgpu_triangle):
```rust
struct MyApp {
    window: Option<&'static Window>,
    // ... your state ...
}

impl ApplicationHandler for MyApp {
    fn resumed(&mut self, event_loop: &ActiveEventLoop) {
        // Create window and initialize wgpu
    }

    fn window_event(&mut self, event_loop: &ActiveEventLoop, id: WindowId, event: WindowEvent) {
        // Handle window events
    }

    fn about_to_wait(&mut self, event_loop: &ActiveEventLoop) {
        // Request redraws
    }
}

